lender.name: Nikolay
lender.loan_because: I borrow money because it’s necessary to sustain and enlarge the business project for dilution quail’s farms.
lender.occupational_info:
The business plan for development quail’s farms for $8-10 thousand
Situation Quail’s eggs - valuable, even a medical product. They contain a lot of vitamins and trace substances even when cholesterol is absent completely. Quails "have won" popularity abroad long time ago where their eggs use not only in the culinary and medical purposes but also as raw materials in perfumery production. Quail’s farming - profitable and prospective business. But everyone can’t achieve the success in this, because much depends on ability and your own desires to work. After all caring about quails is completely manual labor. Production All domestic quail’s farming specialize on dilution for oviparous and meat breeds. To oviparous quail’s breeds concern mottled, British black, white English. To meat breeds concern Pharaohs, American broilers. Many quail- fancier multiply Japanese quails. Quail’s cultivation is very profitable business. Profitability of quail’s production reaches 50-70 %. It is necessary to notice, that turnover of quail’s-farming business also s very high. The female quail reaches productive age for 30-40 days and for a year bears more than 280 eggs. The competition in our business is small. I consider, that today the market is not filled in quail’s production absolutely. Considering, that quail’s eggs and meat win more and more popularity at the population. It is possible to speak boldly about a big prospects of this business. How to begin? If you want enter the market, you will be recommended to begin with 700-1 000 quails. Thanks to fruitfulness the livestock of the feathery can already be enlarged to 5 000 individuals in a year . Completely equipped hen house(with 700-1 000 female quails) will manage in $8-10 thousand. But in 6-9 months of work it is possible to cover all expenses. It is possible to purchase eggs or young stock in any reacting economy. An average price of one hatchable egg is $0,10-0,15. The female quail of three-week age will cost about $1,3-2,5. It is necessary to consider, that efficiency of quails at the age of one year decreases in twice. Therefore it is necessary to care of herd innovation regularly. For this purpose parent herd have to be formed and contained, where for one male quail there are three-four females. Egg for sort continuation take from two - a ten-month auk. One year-old quails hammer for meat. To trade with young growth is not less profitable, than with quail’s eggs and meat. There are new farms which support demand for quails in the country with an enviable persistence. The equipment For containing adults it is more convenient use cells from a welded metal grid. There on farms are established the cellular batteries consisting of six cells, equipped with drinking bowls and feeders, small sides for "catching" eggs. In such cellular battery it is possible to place 240-280 quails. In the West it is possible to buy any special equipment for the keeping and breeding quails without problems. In Ukraine such cells you must do by yourself. All cells for the keeping quails, and also incubators established on domestic farms are self-made. If you have no possibility or desire to make cell by yourself, you can order it on the farms that attended some years to breeding quails. And one of this cellular battery from six cells costs near $120-150. Also there is a necessity to establish incubators which are important to increase livestock and regenerate herd. The cost of such incubator is $630-1630(for 1 300-9 000 eggs). The accommodation For the keeping of 700-1 000 adult-quails I will be enough a little room the area of which is 15-20 sq.m. For the keeping of chickens and young stock the additional room with area about 5 sq.m. And incubators, storage and preparation of feedstuff need an auxiliary premise with the area of 10 sq.m. Of course it is necessary to remember about dilating because at the normal keeping yours 700-1 000 female quails in a year will turn to 5 000. Food supply First of all for preparation of own feed mixture it’s necessary to have a shucker. The shucker costs about $110. Feedstuff costs about $225-325 for tonne. Sales Most of quail’s eggs is selling in the markets and supermarkets, a quail’s carcass deliver mainly in restaurants. But, considering dietary and even medical properties of quail’s eggs, it is possible to try to adjust their sales in a rest houses, kindergartens, sanatoriums and on camp sites. While wholesale market of quail’s meat won’t be generated, the majority of farms delivers their production directly in retail points. One kg of quail’s meat costs $5-8,5. The storage time of quail’s eggs is sufficiently great (in room temperature eggs can store near 30 days, in a fridge near 60 days). For the same reason there are quite attainable markets not only a native city, but also in a nearby settlements.
